Class BinaryTreeNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • BinaryTreeNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Visitable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CosNode, DivideNode, LogNode, MultiplyNode, OperandNode, PowerNode, SinNode, SqrtNode, SubtractNode, SumNode

    public class BinaryTreeNode
extends java.lang.Object
implements Visitable
    BinaryTreeNode class represents a node in the parse tree. It is the base for all the types of nodes in the tree: operator nodes and operand nodes. It implements the Visitable interface, assuring that all the classes that extend are also visitable. The class has a member info, which contains the information in the node: either a symbol for operators, or a number for operands, a member index, which is the index of the nodes in the order in which they were added in the tree, and members leftNode and rightNode, which are references to left and right subtrees respectively, in the parse tree.
    Author:
    Diana
